title: Refactor logic task
body: ## Purpose of the pull request ### Background DolphinScheduler is composed by APIServer/Master/Worker/AlertServer. Master is used to bootstrap a workflow, and worker is used to execute task. Right now, we have two kinds of task in DS: - WorkerTask: Shell, Spark, Sql...... - LogicTask: Condition, Switch, Dependent...... The logic task will be executed in Master, this is due to the logic task will dependent DS's metadata database, and we don't want the worker rely on db, so these logic task will be executed at Master. The current problem is the logic task's trigger process is different with worker task, this led below issue: - The workflow's execution process is very complex, these cause a lot of bug, mainly in logic task. - It's hard to add a new logic task plugin, since we need to consider how to trigger the logic and how to finished it. - The logic task SPI is different with worker task. - Task instance log is hard to maintain. - The logic task execute process will affect other workflow instance, since it use workflow's thread pool. - ...... So, we need to unify these two kinds task's execution process. This PR will refactor the logic task execution in master. ### Detail #### WofkflowExecuteRunnable VS TaskExecuteRunnable WorkflowExecuteRunnable is represent a running workflow instance, it will contain TaskExecuteRunnable, one TaskExecuteRunnable represent a running task instance. All task in the WorkflowExecuteRunnable is as TaskExecuteRunnable, workflow instance only need to maintain the TaskExecuteRunnable, and call TaskExecuteRunnable's api to control task instance. TaskExecuteRunnabel contain some TaskOperator, TaskOperator is use to operate task instance. Each task operation is corresponding to a TaskOperator, e.g TaskDispatchOperator is used dispatch task instance. TaskKillOperator is used to kill task instance.... #### TaskOperator TaskOperator will do actual operation. For example, TaskDispatchOperator is used to dispatch task instance, it will send the task instance to a TaskDispatchWaitingQueue, and a looper thread will loop this queue and dispatch the task instance. If the task instance need to execute at worker, dispatcher will select a worker host to dispatch, if the task instance is a logic task, dispatcher will dispatch these task to itself. #### LogicTaskExecuteThreadPool The LogicTask will use a isolated threadpool to execute the task. And when master receive a LogicTask dispatch request, the process is same with worker, it will create a MasterTaskExecuteRunnable to represent the physical task, and submit it to MasterTaskExecuteRunnableThreadPool. After the LogicTask execute finished, it will send the result to the master like worker task. ## Brief change log ## Verify this pull request This pull request is code cleanup without any test coverage. *(or)* This pull request is already covered by existing tests, such as *(please describe tests)*.
